      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:6:127:2",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) إِذَا أَكَلْتُمُ الْقِثَّاءَ فَكُلُوهُ مِنْ أَسْفَلِهِ فَإِنَّهُ أَعْظَمُ لِبَرَكَتِهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Abdullah Bin Ja’far, from Muhammad Bin Isa, from Ubeydullah Al Dahqan, from dorost Al Wasity, from Abdullah Bin Sinan who said, ",
          "‘Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘When you eat the cucumbers, so eat it from its lower part, for it is greater in its Blessing’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from ‘Abd Allah ibn Ja‘far from Muhammad ibn ‘Isa from ‘Abd Allah al-Dihqan from Durust al- Wasitiy from ‘Abd Allah ibn Sinan who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘When you eat cucumber, eat it from the bottom because it is greater for blessing.”’ "
        ]
      }
    },
